    <item>
      <title>EDM 2650 Letter to my MP</title>
      <link>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/edm-2650_letter_to_my_mp/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 27 Jan 2026 09:18:38 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/edm-2650_letter_to_my_mp/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Subject:&lt;/strong&gt; Support the EDM 2650 - the UK needs a digital sovereignty strategy now&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &lt;picture class=&#34;main-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &#xA;&#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;                &#xA;                &#xA;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/technology_1907_hu_d84df3e26af326cb.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(max-width: 767px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/technology_1907_hu_6e342a150dea6b9a.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(min-width: 768px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;a href=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/technology_1907_hu_6e342a150dea6b9a.jpg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/technology_1907_hu_6e342a150dea6b9a.jpg&#34;  alt=&#34;Illustration from Punch 1907 of two figures in a park, reading telegrams sent via ariels on their hats.&#34;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;            &#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Dear Charlotte Cane MP,&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I urge you to support the EDM 2650, to create an urgently needed UK digital sovereignty strategy.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve been working in the tech sector in the UK for 30 years, and am keenly aware of how fundamentally beholden private and public organisations digital services are to foreign companies. Whether it&amp;rsquo;s the well-known, like Google or Microsoft, or the less visible Palantir, Oracle or AWS - our entire digital infrastructure is owned and run primarily by US tech companies.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Wait, you&#39;re still on X?</title>
      <link>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/wait-you-are-still-on-x/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 14 Jan 2026 11:01:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/wait-you-are-still-on-x/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &lt;picture class=&#34;main-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &#xA;&#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;                &#xA;                &#xA;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/elon-musk_hu_409c9324e62ffbb7.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(max-width: 767px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/elon-musk_hu_c3895da5fecc0928.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(min-width: 768px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;a href=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/elon-musk_hu_c3895da5fecc0928.jpg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/elon-musk_hu_c3895da5fecc0928.jpg&#34;  alt=&#34;Elon Musk looks down on you, but still takes the money that you create for him&#34;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;            &#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;figcaption&gt;Elon Musk&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;OK. So, you ignored warnings &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#x9;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/why-are-you-still-on-x/&#34; &#xA; &#xA;target=&#34;&#34;&#xA;class=&#34;relative&#34; &#xA;data-domain=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;link-text&#34;&gt;like mine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;hostname-text&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; from a year ago, and you&amp;rsquo;re still using and promoting the non-consensual porn and &lt;abbr title=&#34;child sexual abuse material&#34;&gt;CSAM&lt;/abbr&gt; site, x.com.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;😢 &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;We know it&amp;rsquo;s bad, but we&amp;rsquo;ve got a huge audience there.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;But, if that&amp;rsquo;s true, what does that say about your audience? An audience that comprises of supporters of fascism; creators of inappropriate, offensive, and illegal content; and politically weaponised bots? Is this the audience you want to cultivate?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Alternatives in UK</title>
      <link>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/alternatives-in-uk/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 24 Feb 2025 17:51:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/alternatives-in-uk/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;If the UK is to become anything other than a digital vassal of the US, we have to have a nose-to-tail digital service infrastructure&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &lt;picture class=&#34;main-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &#xA;&#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;                &#xA;                &#xA;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/alt-uk_share_preview_hu_13b3174530b89967.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(max-width: 767px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/alt-uk_share_preview_hu_b355c7d9f4f01e6b.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(min-width: 768px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;a href=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/alt-uk_share_preview_hu_b355c7d9f4f01e6b.jpg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/alt-uk_share_preview_hu_b355c7d9f4f01e6b.jpg&#34;  alt=&#34;The alternatives in the UK logo&#34;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;            &#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;What I mean is&amp;hellip; how many digital products, platforms and services are built on Big Tech foundations? It&amp;rsquo;s incredibly hard to find UK owned &lt;em&gt;and&lt;/em&gt; run services. Many, many service-tier offerings (after all, we&amp;rsquo;re a nation of digital greengrocers), but it&amp;rsquo;s quite tricky to find replacements for things like Vercel, Digital Ocean or even Dropbox.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Alternatives to X</title>
      <link>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/alternatives-to-x/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 03 Feb 2025 09:07:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/alternatives-to-x/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &lt;picture class=&#34;main-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &#xA;&#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;                &#xA;                &#xA;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/futami-ga-ura_rocks_at_ise_land_of_dawn_hu_933f29e09ee1e5ee.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(max-width: 767px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/futami-ga-ura_rocks_at_ise_land_of_dawn_hu_efe3f43834e082f.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(min-width: 768px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;a href=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/futami-ga-ura_rocks_at_ise_land_of_dawn_hu_efe3f43834e082f.jpg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/futami-ga-ura_rocks_at_ise_land_of_dawn_hu_efe3f43834e082f.jpg&#34;  alt=&#34;Futami-ga-ura Rocks at Ise, Land of Dawn&#34;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;            &#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;OK, so you&amp;rsquo;ve read my &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#x9;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/why-are-you-still-on-x/&#34; &#xA; &#xA;target=&#34;&#34;&#xA;class=&#34;relative&#34; &#xA;data-domain=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;link-text&#34;&gt;plea to leave X&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;hostname-text&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; , and you&amp;rsquo;re thinking&amp;hellip; ok, they have a point, but&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;how-do-we-start&#34;&gt;How do we start?&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;First of all, I have to acknowledge that this isn&amp;rsquo;t a simple as just deleting your account. Many organisations have had a presence on X (fka Twitter) for a long time and have built up a substantial audience. I&amp;rsquo;m not suggesting you throw that away, yet.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Why are you still on X?</title>
      <link>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/why-are-you-still-on-x/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Jan 2025 11:01:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/why-are-you-still-on-x/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &lt;picture class=&#34;main-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &#xA;&#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;                &#xA;                &#xA;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/elon_salutes1440x960_hu_6c4a389c58d57ef9.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(max-width: 767px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;source srcset=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/elon_salutes1440x960_hu_1d493bacfa997c9.jpg&#34; media=&#34;(min-width: 768px)&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;a href=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/elon_salutes1440x960_hu_1d493bacfa997c9.jpg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://lrg.io/images/elon_salutes1440x960_hu_1d493bacfa997c9.jpg&#34;  alt=&#34;Elon Musk gives a Nazi salute at Donald Trump&amp;#39;s inauguration rally.&#34;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;            &#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;figcaption&gt;Elon Musk gives a Nazi salute at Donald Trump&amp;rsquo;s inauguration rally.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Now that Elon Musk has made his allegiances and motivations pretty clear, I have to ask a question. Why are you still on X?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I get it. You&amp;rsquo;re a big organisation and in some ways, in spite of that size, you&amp;rsquo;re vulnerable if you lose your audience. But, I have to ask again. Why are you still on X?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
